```

Key design decisions:
- `@RefinementAlias("ValidPort(int p) { p >= 0 && p <= 65535 }")` captures the port range constraint used in all 3 bound constructors
- `port` parameters are constrained to `[0, 65535]` per the `IllegalArgumentException` documented in the JSON
- `timeout >= 0` since negative values throw `IllegalArgumentException` per docs
- `size > 0` since zero or negative throws `IllegalArgumentException` per docs
- `getSoTimeout()` returns `_ >= 0` (0 means infinite timeout, so non-negative)
- `getReceiveBufferSize()` returns `_ > 0` (buffer size is always positive)
- `setOption`/`getOption`/`setReuseAddress` are constrained to `unbound` or `bound` states (not `closed`) matching the Mermaid diagram and notes
- `accept()` and `implAccept()` are constrained to `bound` state only
- `close()` has no `from` constraint since it is callable from all states (Unbound, Bound, and Closed)

